<dl id="n05177f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05177f">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05177f"> 177(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> harper on battlefield</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">It is stated indeed that <mark>the bard thus chanted on the old Irish battlefields</mark>, surrounded by a group of harpers, who accompanied him, almost with the effect of a military band. <small> Alfred Perceval Graves, <a name="ILMS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ILMS"><cite title="source">Irish Literary and Musical Studies</cite></a>, (1913) [Folk Song] 182</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
